--- On Mon, 11/12/12, Ed Owens <eowens@eojohnson.com> wrote:

From: Ed Owens <eowens@eojohnson.com>
Subject: [Jukebox-list] Problem, solution. Rockola 484 leaving record and d=
oubling them up In The magazine
To: "Jukebox mailing list" <jukebox-list@lists.netlojix.com>
Date: Monday, November 12, 2012, 12:08 PM

Howdy, just figured I would share my problem and solution.
=A0 Issue, after playing my juke for a day, I noticed empty spots in the ma=
gazine.=A0 Looking further I noticed some records we doubled up.=A0 Some se=
ts were completely in the wrong spot.=A0 This has slowly getting worse and =
worse over the last few weeks.=20
Solution.
=A0 After watching it run after just turning it on I noticed it left a reco=
rd.=A0 What it appeared to do, when camming the gripper closed it would pic=
k the arm up just a hair.=A0 Sometimes this was enough to just miss the rec=
ord.=A0 Then play the next one on top and pick them both up.=20
=A0 What I did was disassemble the gripper arm by taking the gear screw off=
, and pounding the roll pin out.=A0 Out came gripper, arm, cam, and both ge=
ars.=A0 A quick alcohol bath and cleaning with nylon brush and it was ready=
.=A0 I assembled it with Teflon silicone grease.=A0=20
=A0 It now works like a charm.
